<subSubSection id="C32A17AFFFC6DB79B28342F1991593DE" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="587" pageId="9" pageNumber="586" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B8F4424FFC6DB79B28342F1991593DE" blockId="9.[151,1437,1920,2019]" lastBlockId="10.[151,1437,151,393]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="587" pageId="9" pageNumber="586">
<emphasis id="B9449836FFC6DB7AB28342F19C7295CD" bold="true" box="[151,266,1920,1946]" pageId="9" pageNumber="586">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. (
<figureCitation id="130B58A1FFC6DB7AB33542F19CDD95CC" box="[289,421,1920,1947]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–21" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[166,1396,427,1845]" captionTargetId="figure-159@10.[149,1438,417,1853]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 18–21. Saropogon aliyevi, sp. nov., holotype. 18. Head, frontal view. 19. Head and thorax, dorsal view. 20. Habitus, dorsal view. 21. Habitus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4414401" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4414401/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="586">Figs 18–21</figureCitation>
). Body length 12.0–14.0 (
<typeStatus id="548BFA86FFC6DB7AB0D942F19E4995CD" box="[717,817,1920,1946]" pageId="9" pageNumber="586">holotype</typeStatus>
12.0) mm. Mystacal macrosetae white, in lateral view almost reaching apex of proboscis (
<figureCitation id="130B58A1FFC6DB7AB03642D59F0D95E8" box="[546,629,1956,1983]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–21" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[166,1396,427,1845]" captionTargetId="figure-159@10.[149,1438,417,1853]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 18–21. Saropogon aliyevi, sp. nov., holotype. 18. Head, frontal view. 19. Head and thorax, dorsal view. 20. Habitus, dorsal view. 21. Habitus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4414401" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4414401/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="586">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
). Orbital and ocellar setae white; postocular setae and macrosetae white. Antenna brown, scape and pedicel reddish yellow at base, pospedicel reddish yellow at base and middle. Thorax black. Scutum with short white and black setae (
<figureCitation id="130B58A1FFC5DB79B0A745E69E7F92E6" box="[691,775,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–21" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[166,1396,427,1845]" captionTargetId="figure-159@10.[149,1438,417,1853]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 18–21. Saropogon aliyevi, sp. nov., holotype. 18. Head, frontal view. 19. Head and thorax, dorsal view. 20. Habitus, dorsal view. 21. Habitus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4414401" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4414401/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="587">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
). Pleuron silvery tomentose, without setae, katatergite with few white setae and macrosetae (
<figureCitation id="130B58A1FFC5DB79B01245CA9F219282" box="[518,601,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–21" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[166,1396,427,1845]" captionTargetId="figure-159@10.[149,1438,417,1853]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 18–21. Saropogon aliyevi, sp. nov., holotype. 18. Head, frontal view. 19. Head and thorax, dorsal view. 20. Habitus, dorsal view. 21. Habitus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4414401" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4414401/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="587">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
). 1 white dorsocentral setae or none, 2 notopleural, 2 supra- and 2–3 postalar setae white. Scutellum reddish on margin, with 2 white apical macrosetae. Wings are darkened anteroproximally. Fore femur reddish yellow with a dorsal and ventral brown stripe. Mid and hind femora dark brown, reddish yellow at base and apex. Tibiae reddish yellow, dark brown at apex. Fore and mid tarsi dark brown, hind tarsus black. Tergites shiny black with white setae. Tergites I–IV, sometimes V, with reddish brown stripe posteriorly in dorsal view and laterally in lateral view. Hypopygium reddish brown with white setae (
<figureCitation id="130B58A1FFC5DB79B1C9441E991993DE" box="[989,1121,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–21" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[166,1396,427,1845]" captionTargetId="figure-159@10.[149,1438,417,1853]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 18–21. Saropogon aliyevi, sp. nov., holotype. 18. Head, frontal view. 19. Head and thorax, dorsal view. 20. Habitus, dorsal view. 21. Habitus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4414401" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4414401/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="587">Figs 20–21</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF4F14ACFFC5DB79B28342259F6E95C7" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4414401" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4414401" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4414401/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="587" startId="10.[151,264,1876,1900]" targetBox="[166,1396,427,1845]" targetPageId="10">
<paragraph id="8B8F4424FFC5DB79B28342259F6E95C7" blockId="10.[151,1436,1876,1936]" pageId="10" pageNumber="587">
<emphasis id="B9449836FFC5DB79B28342259C2C953B" bold="true" box="[151,340,1876,1900]" pageId="10" pageNumber="587">FIGURES 18–21.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B9449836FFC5DB79B34D42259F6F953B" box="[345,535,1876,1900]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="587">
<taxonomicName id="4C303FA7FFC5DB79B34D42259F6B953B" authority="Sakhvon, 2020" authorityName="Sakhvon" authorityYear="2020" box="[345,531,1876,1900]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Saropogon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aliyevi" status="sp. nov.">Saropogon aliyevi</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B9449836FFC5DB79B00942259F15953B" bold="true" box="[541,621,1876,1900]" pageId="10" pageNumber="587">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A277254DFFC5DB79B00942259F15953B" box="[541,621,1876,1900]" pageId="10" pageNumber="587" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, holotype. 18. Head, frontal view. 19. Head and thorax, dorsal view. 20. Habitus, dorsal view. 21. Habitus, lateral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="C32A17AFFFC4DB7FB2D345E79CB89142" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="589" pageId="11" pageNumber="588" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B8F4424FFC4DB78B2D345E79E8593FB" blockId="11.[151,1437,150,717]" pageId="11" pageNumber="588">
<emphasis id="B9449836FFC4DB78B2D345E79C9292E7" bold="true" box="[199,490,150,176]" pageId="11" pageNumber="588">Description. Male. Head</emphasis>
black. The face is plane. Clypeus and gena reddish. Face with golden brown tomentum. Frons silvery tomentose. Mystax confined to lower facial margin with dense white macrosetae, in lateral view almost reaching apex of proboscis. Distance from upper margin of mystax to antennal sockets longer than length of scape and pedicel combined. First segment of palpus dark brown, second segment reddish brown. Palpus with long white setae. Proboscis dark brown with white setae at base and apex. Orbital setae white. Ocellar setae white, less than length of scape. Postocular setae and macrosetae white. Lower occipital setae white.Antenna brown. Scape and pedicel reddish yellow at base, with white setae, pospedicel reddish yellow at base and in the middle. Style wide and beveled with seta-like sensory element; equal to 1/3 of scape length (
<figureCitation id="130B58A1FFC4DB78B18844E39E9793FB" box="[924,1007,402,428]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–21" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[166,1396,427,1845]" captionTargetId="figure-159@10.[149,1438,417,1853]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 18–21. Saropogon aliyevi, sp. nov., holotype. 18. Head, frontal view. 19. Head and thorax, dorsal view. 20. Habitus, dorsal view. 21. Habitus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4414401" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4414401/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="588">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8F4424FFC4DB78B2D344C79FB890FF" blockId="11.[151,1437,150,717]" pageId="11" pageNumber="588">
<emphasis id="B9449836FFC4DB78B2D344C79C589387" bold="true" box="[199,288,438,464]" pageId="11" pageNumber="588">Thorax</emphasis>
black. Median and paramedian stripes in presutural area of scutum and sutural area silvery tomentose. Scutum with wide stripe of silvery tomentum extending from anterior margin to scutellum in lateral view. Scutum with short white and black setae. Pleuron black, silvery tomentose and without setae, but katatergite with few white setae and macrosetae. Anepimeron reddish dorsally. Postpronotal lobe clearly reddish yellow, silvery tomentose and without setae. Postalar callus reddish with silvery tomentum. Scutellum reddish on margin, with 2 white apical macrosetae; disk silvery tomentose, without setae. Notum with 1 white dorsocentral seta or none. 2 notopleural, 2 supra- and 2–3 postalar setae white (
<figureCitation id="130B58A1FFC4DB78B02447FF9FCC90FF" box="[560,692,654,680]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–21" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[166,1396,427,1845]" captionTargetId="figure-159@10.[149,1438,417,1853]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 18–21. Saropogon aliyevi, sp. nov., holotype. 18. Head, frontal view. 19. Head and thorax, dorsal view. 20. Habitus, dorsal view. 21. Habitus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4414401" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4414401/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="588">Figs 19–20</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8F4424FFC4DB78B2D347C3980A909B" blockId="11.[151,1437,150,717]" box="[199,1394,690,717]" pageId="11" pageNumber="588">
<emphasis id="B9449836FFC4DB78B2D347C39C6B909B" bold="true" box="[199,275,690,716]" pageId="11" pageNumber="588">Wings</emphasis>
are darkened anteroproximally due to dense brown microtrichia along veins, veins brown (
<figureCitation id="130B58A1FFC4DB78B70547C3981E909B" box="[1297,1382,690,716]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–21" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[166,1396,427,1845]" captionTargetId="figure-159@10.[149,1438,417,1853]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 18–21. Saropogon aliyevi, sp. nov., holotype. 18. Head, frontal view. 19. Head and thorax, dorsal view. 20. Habitus, dorsal view. 21. Habitus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4414401" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4414401/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="588">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF4F14ACFFC4DB78B28342D799F895B5" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4414403" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4414403" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4414403/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="588" startId="11.[151,264,1958,1982]" targetBox="[175,1414,753,1917]" targetPageId="11">
<paragraph id="8B8F4424FFC4DB78B28342D799F895B5" blockId="11.[151,1436,1958,2018]" pageId="11" pageNumber="588">
<emphasis id="B9449836FFC4DB78B28342D79C2E95E9" bold="true" box="[151,342,1958,1982]" pageId="11" pageNumber="588">FIGURES 22–26.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B9449836FFC4DB78B34942D79F6595E9" box="[349,541,1958,1982]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="588">
<taxonomicName id="4C303FA7FFC4DB78B34942D79F6195E9" authority="Sakhvon, 2020" authorityName="Sakhvon" authorityYear="2020" box="[349,537,1958,1982]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Saropogon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="588" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aliyevi" status="sp. nov.">Saropogon aliyevi</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B9449836FFC4DB78B03042D79F0E95E9" bold="true" box="[548,630,1958,1982]" pageId="11" pageNumber="588">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A277254DFFC4DB78B03042D79F0E95E9" box="[548,630,1958,1982]" pageId="11" pageNumber="588" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, holotype. 22. Epandrium, dorsal view. 23. Hypandrium and gonopod, ventral view. 24. Gonopod, lateral internal surface. 25. Aedeagus, frontal view. 26. Aedeagus, lateral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8B8F4424FFC3DB7FB2D345E69DBC93FA" blockId="12.[151,1437,151,897]" pageId="12" pageNumber="589">
<emphasis id="B9449836FFC3DB7FB2D345E69D8792E6" bold="true" box="[199,255,151,177]" pageId="12" pageNumber="589">Legs</emphasis>
. Coxae reddish yellow, black laterally, silvery tomentose, with white setae and macrosetae. Trochanters reddish yellow with silvery tomentum. Fore femur reddish yellow with brown stripe dorsally and a light brown one ventrally, not reaching the apex. Mid and hind femora dark brown, reddish yellow at base and apex. Femora and tibiae with white setae. Fore and mid tibiae reddish yellow, dark brown at apex. Hind tibia reddish yellow at 1/3 of its length, dark brown distally. Tibiae with golden macrosetae, some of them brown at apex of tibiae. Fore and mid tarsi dark brown, hind tarsus black, with black macrosetae, some of them golden. Spine on fore tibia black. Claws dark brown, reddish yellow at base. Pulvillus well developed, reddish yellow, longer than 2/3 of claw length (
<figureCitation id="130B58A1FFC3DB7FB77B441E9DCE93FA" captionStart="FIGURES 18–21" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[166,1396,427,1845]" captionTargetId="figure-159@10.[149,1438,417,1853]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 18–21. Saropogon aliyevi, sp. nov., holotype. 18. Head, frontal view. 19. Head and thorax, dorsal view. 20. Habitus, dorsal view. 21. Habitus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4414401" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4414401/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="589">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8F4424FFC3DB7FB2D344C7992193A2" blockId="12.[151,1437,151,897]" pageId="12" pageNumber="589">
<emphasis id="B9449836FFC3DB7FB2D344C79C449387" bold="true" box="[199,316,438,464]" pageId="12" pageNumber="589">Abdomen</emphasis>
. Tergites shiny black with white setae; tergite I with white macrosetae laterally. Tergites I–IV, sometimes V, with reddish brown stripe posteriorly in dorsal and lateral view (
<figureCitation id="130B58A1FFC3DB7FB1DD44AA993493A2" box="[969,1100,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–21" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[166,1396,427,1845]" captionTargetId="figure-159@10.[149,1438,417,1853]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 18–21. Saropogon aliyevi, sp. nov., holotype. 18. Head, frontal view. 19. Head and thorax, dorsal view. 20. Habitus, dorsal view. 21. Habitus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4414401" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4414401/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="589">Figs 20–21</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8F4424FFC3DB7FB2D3448F98169035" blockId="12.[151,1437,151,897]" pageId="12" pageNumber="589">
<emphasis id="B9449836FFC3DB7FB2D3448F9C1B904F" bold="true" box="[199,355,510,536]" pageId="12" pageNumber="589">Hypopygium</emphasis>
reddish brown, rotated 90 
<superScript id="7C45E96CFFC3DB7FB09C448E9FE8905A" attach="left" box="[648,656,511,525]" fontSize="6" pageId="12" pageNumber="589">o</superScript>
to the right, with white setae becoming longer and denser towards the apex. Epandrium divided in the middle into two halves. Gonocoxite elongated, with two narrow process on posterior margin. Aedeagus elongated and curved in the middle. Apodeme of ejaculator large and rounded (
<figureCitation id="130B58A1FFC3DB7FB6CB473698199035" box="[1247,1377,583,610]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 18–21" captionStart-1="FIGURES 22–26" captionStartId-0="10.[151,264,1876,1900]" captionStartId-1="11.[151,264,1958,1982]" captionTargetBox-0="[166,1396,427,1845]" captionTargetBox-1="[175,1414,753,1917]" captionTargetId-0="figure-159@10.[149,1438,417,1853]" captionTargetId-1="figure-275@11.[156,1432,740,1934]" captionTargetPageId-0="10" captionTargetPageId-1="11" captionText-0="FIGURES 18–21. Saropogon aliyevi, sp. nov., holotype. 18. Head, frontal view. 19. Head and thorax, dorsal view. 20. Habitus, dorsal view. 21. Habitus, lateral view." captionText-1="FIGURES 22–26. Saropogon aliyevi, sp. nov., holotype. 22. Epandrium, dorsal view. 23. Hypandrium and gonopod, ventral view. 24. Gonopod, lateral internal surface. 25. Aedeagus, frontal view. 26. Aedeagus, lateral view." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4414401" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4414403" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/4414401/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/4414403/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="589">Figs 21–26</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8F4424FFC3DB7FB2D3471A9E7290D2" blockId="12.[151,1437,151,897]" box="[199,778,619,645]" pageId="12" pageNumber="589">
